{"topics":[{"topicLabel":"Fast and rapid","topicThesaurusName":"topics","topicUrl":"http://dictionary.cambridge.org/topics/moving-quickly-and-slowly/fast-and-rapid/","topicId":"fast-and-rapid","topicParentId":"moving-quickly-and-slowly"}],"dictionaryCode":"american-english","entryLabel":"crash","entryContent":"<di><header><title>crash<\/title><\/header> <pos-block><header><info><posgram><pos>noun<\/pos> <gram>[<gcs><gc>C<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/posgram> <audio type=\"pronunciation\" region=\"us\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron/c/cra/crash/crash.mp3\"/><source type=\"audio/ogg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron_ogg/c/cra/crash/crash.ogg\"/><\/audio> <pron>/<ipa>kræʃ<\/ipa>/<\/pron> <\/info><\/header><sense-block><header><title>ACCIDENT<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <\/info><def>a serious accident in which one or more cars, trucks, or other vehicles hit something, or in which an aircraft hits the ground or another aircraft: <\/def><\/definition><examp><eg>She was killed in an airplane crash in 1983.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>NOISE<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <\/info><def>a loud noise that sounds as if it is caused by something violently breaking apart or hitting something else: <\/def><\/definition><examp><eg>There was a loud crash, and we rushed over to see what had fallen.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>FAILURE<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <\/info><def>a sudden loss of value of investments, or a failure of a business<\/def><\/definition><\/def-block><\/sense-block><\/pos-block> <pos-block><header><info><posgram><pos>verb<\/pos><\/posgram> <audio type=\"pronunciation\" region=\"us\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron/c/cra/crash/crash.mp3\"/><source type=\"audio/ogg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron_ogg/c/cra/crash/crash.ogg\"/><\/audio> <pron>/<ipa>kræʃ<\/ipa>/<\/pron> <\/info><\/header><sense-block><header><title>GO WHERE NOT INVITED<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>T<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram> <lab><usage>infml<\/usage><\/lab><\/info> <def>to go to a party or other event without an invitation: <\/def><\/definition><examp><eg>Some guys tried to crash the party but they weren\u2019t allowed in.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>SLEEP<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>I<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram> <lab><usage>slang<\/usage><\/lab><\/info> <def>to sleep, or to stay at a place to sleep temporarily: <\/def><\/definition><examp><eg>I was so tired after work, I crashed on the sofa.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>NOISE<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>always<\/gc> <gc>+ adv/prep<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>to fall or hit something in a noisy or violent way: <\/def><\/definition><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>I<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>All the dishes the waitress was carrying crashed to the floor.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>always<\/gc> <gc>+ adv/prep<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>To crash is also to move in a noisy or violent way: <\/def><\/definition><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>I<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>A big black bear came crashing through the underbrush.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>FAIL<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>I<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>(of investments) to lose value, or (of a business) to lose money and be unable to continue to operate: <\/def><\/definition><examp><eg>When the market crashed, everyone lost money.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>I<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>If a computer crashes, it suddenly stops operating.<\/def><\/definition><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>HIT VIOLENTLY<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>I/T<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>(of a vehicle on the ground) to hit another vehicle or a large object violently, or (of an aircraft) to fall and violently hit the ground, a building, etc., or hit another aircraft while flying: <\/def><\/definition><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>I<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>The plane crashed into the mountainside, killing all aboard.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block><\/pos-block> <pos-block><header><info><posgram><pos>adjective<\/pos><\/posgram> <audio type=\"pronunciation\" region=\"us\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron/c/cra/crash/crash.mp3\"/><source type=\"audio/ogg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron_ogg/c/cra/crash/crash.ogg\"/><\/audio> <pron>/<ipa>kræʃ<\/ipa>/<\/pron> <lab><usage>infml<\/usage><\/lab><\/info><\/header> <sense-block><header><title>QUICK<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <\/info><def>involving great effort to achieve a lot quickly: <\/def><\/definition><examp><eg>took a crash course in cooking<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <\/info><def>A crash diet is a way of losing body weight quickly by eating very little.<\/def><\/definition><\/def-block><\/sense-block><\/pos-block><footer><copyright>(Definition of crash  from the <x href=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/american-english/\" title=\"Cambridge Academic Content Dictionary\n\">Cambridge Academic Content Dictionary\n<\/x> © Cambridge University Press)<\/copyright><\/footer><\/di>\n","entryUrl":"http://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/american-english/crash","format":"xml","entryId":"crash"}